<p>The <code>check</code> tag checks if a record exists.</p>

<h2>Syntax</h2>
<pre>{open}check "table where condition"{close}
  Record exists
{open}else{close}
  Record not found
{open}/check{close}</pre>

<h2>Example: User Exists</h2>
<pre>{open}check "users where username = 'admin'"{close}
  &lt;p&gt;Admin user exists&lt;/p&gt;
{open}else{close}
  &lt;p&gt;Admin user not found&lt;/p&gt;
{open}/check{close}</pre>

<h2>PHP Variable Method</h2>
<pre>// In PHP:
$hasAdmin = db("check users where username = 'admin'");

// In template:
{open}if $hasAdmin{close}
  Admin exists
{open}/if{close}</pre>

<h2>Use Cases</h2>
<ul>
  <li>Validate before insert (check duplicates)</li>
  <li>Authorization checks</li>
  <li>Feature availability</li>
</ul>

<h2>Note</h2>
<p>More efficient than {open}record{close} when you only need to know if data exists.</p>
